1 Reboot your computer
Hold shift during reboot to start GRUB menu
Highlighten the os and press e to edit
find the line starting with 'linux' and append rw init=/bin/bash at the end of the line.
Press Ctrl + X to boot
it will boot into root@none
type passwd to change password
type your new password and confirm your new password
done. restart your machine and enjoy .your new root password is set
